children.subject: No one in Computer Science can answer that question because we are not managing enrollment for the class in F18. Please re-read the FAQ to see where to post a question like this. I believe the instructors have a different message board for posting/answering questions.

If you read the FAQ page closely enough, you should have noticed this:

Q. If I fill out this form, how will my enrollment be processed?

A. Students who meet the pre/coreqs will be enrolled first, then space permitting, those who filled out the form will be admitted according to the order of the waitlist.

Form signatories will be processed for the first time after Phase I enrollment is completed for all continuing students. We will update this FAQ with an exact date soon.
I have filled the appeals form and submitted it successfully. Does this mean that I can enroll in C100 now?

history.content:
The STAT department is managing enrollments for C100 in F18 but we do have some handy information to share:

     1. For the first time, PRE-REQUISITES ARE BEING APPLIED TO C100 which means you cannot (easily) enroll into the class if you do not meet the pre-reqs.

     2. There is an appeals process if you believe you should be allowed to enroll in the class. You will find a link to the appeals form along with instructions in the FAQ document.

If you have further questions after reading this post, please follow the steps in the FAQ.
